Summary Global death toll passes 20,000; confirmed cases 450,000; 110,000 people have recovered A quarter of the world's population is now living under some form of lockdown New York reports more than 25,000 cases but the governor says social distancing appears to be working President Donald Trump promises the US economy will take off "like a rocket ship" once the situation improves Prince Charles - heir to the British throne - tests positive for virus with "mild symptoms", palace says India's 1.3 billion people went into lockdown at midnight, with a "total ban" on leaving homes Russia's Putin postpones vote on constitutional change allowing him to stay in power The death toll in Spain has overtaken China, in Italy cases fall slightly from Tuesday